Apps are => collection of connected components
	4 types of components: Activity, Content Provider, Service, BroadCast Receiver
	all of the components are registered in android manifest

Activity: is the android component responsible for most app user interaction
	: responsible for creating the window that your application uses to
		draw and receive events from the system
	: each activity contains a layout that provides teh system with detailed
	: ac activity determines what views to create by reading an XML layout file.
res folder => where android stores application resources
layout => android stores all of its layout files in XML format

FrameLayout, Linear Layout, Constraint Layout are the most common layout.
FrameLayout:  is great for simple layout when you only have one child view
LinearLayout: great for stacking views vertically or horizantally one after another.


